				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In this lesson I’m going to show you how to really spice up your pentatonic scales… <strong>with just 2 notes!</strong></p>
<p>By simply adding in the 2 notes I'm going to show you in this lesson it’s going to give your lines a completely different vibe… and the best thing is, you don’t have to learn a heaps of <a href="https://www.scottsbasslessons.com/improvisation/break-free-old-pentatonic-scale-shape.html">new shapes</a> or <a href="https://www.scottsbasslessons.com/improvisation/one-hippest-scales-youll-ever-learn.html">fancy scales</a>…</p>
<p>You can add these 2 notes into a simple scale you’ll already know!</p>
<p>Give it a try… and let me know how you get along in the comments under the video :)</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed…</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
