		<title>How to play epic gospel bass fills&#8230;</title>
		<link>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/play-epic-gospel-bass-fills.html</link>
		<comments>http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/play-epic-gospel-bass-fills.html#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Thu, 02 Mar 2017 13:10:14 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[scott]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Bass Lines & Grooves]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Improvisation]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/?p=16269</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>=== Ok… let’s talk GOSPEL CHOPS! We’ve all heard epic gospel players such as Sharay Reed, Justin Raines and Fred Hammond tearing it up with those crazy sounding gospel bass fills… And let’s get it straight… we ALL want to...</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/bass-lines-grooves/play-epic-gospel-bass-fills.html">How to play epic gospel bass fills&#8230;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com">Online Bass Lessons</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/Qlxf-Xue1o8" width="560" height="315" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen"></iframe></p>
<p>===</p>
<p>Ok… let’s talk GOSPEL CHOPS!</p>
<p>We’ve all heard epic gospel players such as Sharay Reed, Justin Raines and Fred Hammond tearing it up with those crazy sounding gospel bass fills…</p>
<p>And let’s get it straight… we ALL want to get those into our playing, right?! ;)</p>
<p><b>Well, in this lesson I’m going to show you: </b></p>
<ul>
<li>How to work those gospel style bass fills into your playing</li>
<li>2 scales you can use to achieve that gospel sound</li>
<li>And an AWESOME exercise that will enable you to get your hammer-ons and pull-offs together (this is a big deal for getting the correct feel within your gospel style bass fills)</li>
</ul>
<p><b>Ok… question for you guys…</b></p>
<p>Who are your favourite gospel bass players… and what albums with them playing on should I check out? As you can imagine… I’m a TOTAL bass nerd and love finding out about what and who you guys are listening too… make sure you let me know by leaving a comment below the video!</p>
<p>As always, see you in the shed…</p>
<p>Scott :)</p>
<p>PS. If you’re going to be coming along to the London Bass Show this weekend (March 4th and 5th) I’m going to be there with the SBL team… plus we’re going to have our own room and will be running 4 workshops per day with SBL faculty members such as Cody Wright, Zoltan Dekany, Steve Lawson, Phil Mann, Chris May, Stefan Redtenbacher, Geoff Chalmers… and me!</p>
<p>If you wanna check out the time for each of the workshops <a href="http://www.scottsbasslessons.com/notes/sbl-bass-workshop.html" target="_blank">[click here]</a> (you can also grab a 20% discount for your tickets via that page too).</p>
<p>We’re also going to have a meet up on each day too at 3.30pm around the cafe within the show…</p>
<p>It’d be amazing to meet you… so if you’re coming along, grab me and say hi!</p>
